          "username": "krisjinka"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2018-08-20 01:01:56.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\n> (1 comment)\n\nActually, the server list is expected to have only 1 entry. because i looked at the usage, it seems, we only consider first element and not the rest. getServers().get(0). Hence based on this, ==1 seems to be correct, if the first element is empty, then it is invalid, \nValid:\n1) {\"127.0.0.1\"}\n\n\nInvalid:\n1) {\"\", \"127.0.0.1\"}\n2) {\" \", \"127.0.0.1\"}\n\nAre there any other scenarios ?",
        "patchset_number": 4
      },
